p.q:
That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to provide for the establishment of a public board with the function of promoting the ability of the shipbuilding industry in the United Kingdom to compete in world markets. it is expedient to authorise—


A. The issue out of the Consolidated Fund of sums to be paid by the Minister of Technology to the board and to be used by it for making loans not together exceeding £32,500,000.

B. The payment out of moneys provided by Parliament of—


1) sums to be paid by the Minister to the board and to be used by it—


a) for making grants which except in so far as they are in relief of interest on loans made by the board) do not together exceed £5,150,000;

b) for meeting expenditure on subscribing for shares, being expenditure which when taken together with loans made by the board, does not exceed the amount specified in paragraph A above;

c) for meeting the expenditure of the board so far as it does not consist of grants or loans made by the board or of expenditure on subscribing for shares;


2) any sums required by the Minister for fulfilling guarantees given by him in connection with the construction of ships in shipyards situated in the United Kingdom and the equipment of ships constructed in such shipyards, so however that his total


liability at any time in respect of such guarantees exclusive of any liability in respect of interest on any principal moneys the payment of which is the subject of any such guarantee) shall not exceed £200,000,000;

3) any expenses incurred by the Minister in consequence of any provision of that Act whereby property, rights and liabilities of the board are transferred to him on its dissolution:

4) any administrative expenses incurred by the Minister for the purposes of that Act

5) any sum required by that Act to be paid by the Minister into the Exchequer in connection with the issue of shares in satisfaction of a loan made by the board;


C. Borrowing for the purposes of the Act in any manner authorised by the National Loans Act 1939

D. The payment into the Exchequer of any sums falling to be so paid by virtue of the said Act of the present Session and the re-issue out of the Consolidated Fund of such of those sums as fall to be so re-issued by virtue of that Act.—[Mr. Benn.]
